{
  "text": "One of the earliest mass-enlistments of end-users via software toolkits, is in the computer games area [CITATION_1] , where numerous games have tens of millions of users, and several of them have tens of thousands of end-users providing additional innovative content and functionality to those games. Prugl and Schreier [CITATION_2] studied the use of toolkits for the popular computer game The Sims (28 million units sold within 2 years of release), in which they studied samples from four online user communities, with an average of 15,000 members (ibid). Many other games offer toolkits to end-users to extend game functionality and content. Jeppesen and Molin [CITATION_3] found that of the 94 games they surveyed, 33 of them included toolkits for end-user development.",
  "citation_candidates": [
